[0.181, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[1;15Hh\u001b[3;4Hhe following modules are loaded before any boot h\u001b[4;31Hh\u001b[5;7Hh\u001b[6;19Hhid xhci_h\u001b[10;4Hh\u001b[11;6Hh into the CPIO image.  Th\u001b[12;13Hhe actual binaries included by a given h\u001b[17;4Hhis setting is similar to BINARIES above, h\u001b[18;42Hh\u001b[22;4Hhis is the most important setting in this file.  The HOOKS control th\u001b[23;33Hhe image, and what h\u001b[24;46Hhat you do not change th\u001b[25;13Hhich HOOKS are added.  Run 'mkinitcpio -H <h\u001b[26;3Hhelp on a given h\u001b[27;51Hh\u001b[31;7Hhis setup specifies all modules in th\u001b[35;7Hhis setup will autodetect all modules for your system and sh\u001b[39;7Hhis setup will generate a 'full' image which\u001b[43;7Hhis setup assembles a mdadm array with\u001b[47;7Hh\u001b[50;7Hhis will create a systemd based initramfs which\u001b[53;19Hhave /usr on a separate partition, you MUST include th\u001b[54;19Hh\u001b[58;8Hhis to compress th\u001b[70;27Hh\u001b[74;226H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f \u001b[75;2H\u001b[?25h"]
